						<h2 align= 'center'> <font color='midnightblue'>Master Of Business Administration </font></h2><br/>
							<img src="pics/busmng.jpg"><br/><br/><br/>
						<p>
						<b>Chandigarh Group of Colleges offer</b> a 2 year MBA (Masters of Business Administration Programme) (full time) approved by AICTE New Delhi and Govt. of Punjab and has an affiliation to Punjab Technical University (PTU) Jalandhar. The Masters of Business Administration degree course focuses on instilling strategic and creative awareness to make future business leaders. The course is designed to bring students close to business reality and make him/ her aware of socio-economic, global cultural and technological contexts.<br/><br/>
						
						<span>Future Prospect of Course</span><br/><br/>
						 
							A Masters of Business Administration degree from a reputed business school opens up global career opportunities. Revolution in manufacturing, communications, and transportation technologies has cultivated innovation and that too in an extraordinary way. The rapid changing business scenario seeks young and dynamic business professionals with new mindset, who will be performing in an ever-changing environment. Certainly, a knowledgeable executive is capable to reach the top in the management ladder to become President or CEO with hefty pay package and perks.<br/><br/>
 						
 						<span>Placements Details</span><br/><br/>
 								After nonstop record-breaking placement seasons in the last few years and constant student feedback, the senior team at Chandigarh Group of Colleges (CGC Landran) has taken an initiative to simplify the whole process of training and placements.  Our CGC team is comprised of large number of senior academicians, industry experts to brain storm and discuss the necessary skill sets which a student requires to get placed in the best companies. <br/>
 								On the basis of recommendations of our expert team, the Training and Placement Program (TPP) works on the prime objective of making students Industry-ready and make sure that each students gets placed quickly. <br/>
 								A few of our recruiters comprises - Moser Baer India Ltd, Al Kay&rsquo;s International, Royal Bank of Scotland, Bajaj Electricals, Ralson Tyres Ltd, HT Media and many more.
						
						<span>Industrial Interface</span><br/><br/>
						We are adopting the globally relevant practices to create a continuous stream of future student leaders and continuously improving upon the past.<br/>
						By understanding the industry requirements, we have developed a deep insight which helps our students to get industry ready in a short span of time.<br/>
						The initiatives are executed through Institute Industry Partnership Cell (IIPC) and Corporate Resource Centre (CRC) which are continuously working in synchronization with the corporate leaders to develop a deep bond between the industry and CBSA.<br/>
 						
 						<ul>
 						
 						<li><b>Industry Institute Partnership Cell (IIPC)</b></li><br/>
 						<p>Industry Institute Partnership Cell I at CBSA aims to foster good working relationship between CGC and partner industries. Our joint ventures comprise of planning and conduct of academic events such as: National Conferences, Seminars and Workshops, Guest Lectures by reputed professionals and many more.<br/>
						</p>
						
						<li><b>Entrepreneur Development Cell (EDC)</b></li><br/>
						<p>EDC is established with a view to give fillip to the budding entrepreneurs. Regular programmes are conducted for the volunteer students to create awareness as well as to hone their skills which are quite essential for success in entrepreneurial ventures. Experts from academia and industry address the students to guide and motivate them to turn their dreams into reality.<br/>
						</p>
						
						<li><b>Management Development Projects (MDP)</b></li><br/>
						<p>Management Development Projects are taken up quickly at campus. These projects include training programmes conducted or the various companies, both at campus as well as at their respective locations. Our MDPs are custom made to meet the specific needs of the companies and delivered with the professional touch to ensure effectiveness.<br/><br/>
 						</p>
 						</ul>
 						
 						<span>Eligibility Criteria</span><br/><br/> 
							Candidate must hold a three-year bachelor's degree in any discipline from a renowned University. 66.6% seats from the state quota and 33.3% are Management Quota Seats.<br/><br/>
 
 						<span>Admission Process</span><br/><br/>
							 Admissions are done on the basis of Graduation marks and to get admission in the Best MBA College of Chandigarh (CGC Landran) you must have to clear the eligibility criteria. 
